originalText.text:
We went to Clinton St for brunch on a recommendation! On a weekday also they are busy so make your way down there a bit handy to avoid the peak brunch hour ! Luckily we only had to wait 10 - 15 min to be seated!

We ordered the fried chicken waffle, green salad and sausages !

The flavour in the waffle was really good , would have liked some crunch on the fried chicken , overall the dish worked with the warm maple butter served on the side!

The green salad added a good freshness!

The flavour and texture of the sausages was hugely disappointing!

We tried their pancakes at a different location - time out market (Dumbo, Brooklyn) and hands down these were the best blueberry pancakes weâ€™ve ever had! They are popular for their pancakes and they live up to that expectation! So fresh, soft melt in the mouth , perfect with the blueberry sauce and warm maple butter !! Every bite sings in your mouth ! Definitely recommend!

Overall a good place for brunch with an American diner vibe !

originalText.text:
Clinton Street Baking Company is one of those places where there is nothing left to be said. Which is why I never felt the need to pen a review. With over 5,000 favorable remarks that span a decade plus, they are a NYC staple.

So what more can be said, nothing really except for give them a try if you haven't already. As many may know their popularity requires you to pack your patience because you may definitely experience a wait. However, you won't be disappointed. The cozy atmosphere, wonderful service and great food will make up for the time spent waiting for a table.

On my last visit Matthew was simply a pleasure and provided my bestie with a birthday pancake serenade and we loved it.

Just A Note:

The Blueberry Pancakes are a must try!

originalText.text: This restaurant deserves its rank for having the best pancakes in New York. They are absolutely delicious! Iâ€™ve tried the blueberry and chocolate chip so far but I have no doubt that the banana walnut is delicious too. Everyone must try the grits. OMG they are so good! I like the restaurant so much that last year I celebrated my birthday over there with all my closest friends. Everyone said very nice things about the food. Two of my friends had the fried chicken and waffles. They liked it very much. My other friends had rave reviews for the shrimp and grits. Everyone must also try the biscuits and raspberry jam. They are very good! We all ate them up. This is truly a great restaurant. I highly recommend everyone to try the pancakes.
